abundance.%26quot%3B%20It%20became%20possible%20and%20desirable%20to%20constantly%20have%20more%2C%20in%20order%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20Joneses%20and%20with%20our%20own%20ideals%20of%20consumerism.%20%26quot%3BThe%20culture%20of%20consumption%20that%20we%20have%20is%20absolutely%20predicated%20on%20supercheap%20stuff%20that%20we%20can%20easily%20throw%20away%20and%20not%20have%20to%20worry%20about%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20consumer%20economy%20is%20a%20driving%20force%20in%20the%20American%20economic%20engine.%20We%20spend%20money%20to%20keep%20the%20wheels%20turning.%20It's%20become%20part%20of%20our%20patriotic%20duty%20%E2%80%94%20after%20the%20September%2011%2C%202001%2C%20attacks%2C%20political%20leaders%20told%20Americans%20to%20keep%20spending%20and%20not%20let%20what%20happened%20%26quot%3Bin%20any%20way%20throw%20off%20their%20normal%20level%20of%20activity.%26quot%3B%20The%20ability%20to%20spend%20on%20what%20we%20want%20when%20we%20want%20is%20viewed%20as%20a%20pillar%20of%20American%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%2C%20there's%20no%20shame%20in%20being%20materialistic.%20In%20fact%2C%20materialism%20is%20part%20of%20our%20consumer%20citizenship%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Wendy%20Woloson%2C%20a%20history%20professor%20at%20Rutgers%20University%20who%20is%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BCrap%3A%20A%20History%20of%20Cheap%20Stuff%20in%20America.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20churn%20of%20stuff%20cuts%20across%20income%20levels%2C%20too.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewconsumer.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2FConsumer-Trends-2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20The%20New%20Consumer%20and%20Coefficient%20Capital%20found%20that%20Shein%20shoppers%20were%20likelier%20to%20say%20they%20cared%20about%20sustainability%20and%20the%20environment%20than%20the%20average%20consumer%20%E2%80%94%20eyebrow-raising%2C%20given%20that%20Shein's%20clothes%20and%20business%20model%20are%20pointedly%20not%20good%20for%20the%20planet.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.earnestanalytics.com%2Finsights%2Ftemu-growing-fastest-among-high-income-earners%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOver%252044%2525%2520of%2520Temu%2527s%2520sales%2Coutgrow%2520lower%2520income%2520earning%2520segments.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseparate%20March%202024%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20credit%20card%20data%20company%20Earnest%20Analytics%20found%20that%20nearly%20half%20of%20sales%20for%20Temu%2C%20another%20cheap%20Chinese%20retail%20marketplace%2C%20came%20from%20people%20making%20over%20%24130%2C000%20a%20year.%20Given%20the%20way%20wealth%20has%20been%20concentrated%20at%20the%20tippy%20top%20of%20the%20economy%2C%20it%20tracks%3A%20Nearly%20everyone%20outside%20the%20top%2010%25%20of%20income%20earners%20is%20feeling%20squeezed%20by%20costs%20of%20things%20such%20as%20healthcare%20and%20higher%20education%2C%20and%20cheap%20consumer%20goods%20are%20an%20outlet%20to%20exercise%20some%20agency.%20And%20in%20uncertain%20economic%20times%2C%20everyone's%20feeling%20a%20little%20price-sensitive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration's%20recent%20moves%20have%20some%20important%20implications%20for%20the%20cheap-stuffification%20of%20the%20American%20economy.%20The%20president%20is%20taking%20a%20protectionist%20approach%20to%20trade%2C%20implementing%20tariffs%20that%20could%20make%20the%20inexpensive%20things%20consumers%20have%20come%20to%20rely%20on%20quite%20a%20bit%20more%20expensive.%20Retailers%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftarget-best-buy-ceo-warns-higher-prices-increases-trump-tariffs-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBest%20Buy%20and%20Target%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20begun%20to%20warn%20of%20price%20increases.%20The%20stream%20of%20super-low-cost%20inane%20items%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-impact-shein-temu-sales-de-minimis-uncertainty-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShein%20and%20Temu%20could%20be%20cut%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20get%20his%20way.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-trump-tariffs-will-impact-prices-technology-clothes-appliances-furniture-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprices%20of%20clothes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20electronics%2C%20and%20toys%20are%20likely%20to%20go%20up%20%E2%80%94%20the%20things%20that%20up%20until%20now%20have%20been%20reliably%20affordable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20whole%20agenda%20is%20let's%20make%20it%20so%20that%20it's%20not%20the%20default%20option%20to%20buy%20just%20the%20cheapest%2C%20crappiest%20stuff%20from%20overseas%20when%20we%20should%20be%20making%20more%20of%20it%20in%20America%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dan%20Frommer%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20editor%20in%20chief%20of%20The%20New%20Consumer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20shifting%20the%20entire%20supply%20chain%20for%20goods%20from%20overseas%20back%20into%20the%20US%20is%20a%20transition%20that%2C%20if%20it%20happens%2C%20will%20be%20painful%20for%20consumers.%20We're%20used%20to%20a%20world%20of%20more%20more%20more%20%E2%80%94%20we%20don't%20know%20what%20it's%20like%20to%20do%20less%20less%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20have%20that%20experience%20of%20contraction.%20The%20system%20has%20grown%20and%20grown%20and%20grown%20and%20grown%20and%20grown%2C%20and%20the%20system%20is%20based%20on%20growing%20and%20growing%20and%20growing%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Susan%20Strasser%2C%20a%20historian%20of%20American%20consumer%20culture.%20%26quot%3BYou%20want%20the%20end%20of%20the%20quarter%20report%20to%20be%20better%20than%20the%20last%20end%20of%20the%20quarter%20report.%20That's%20the%20whole%20point%20of%20it.%20And%20so%20in%20no%20sense%20are%20people%20prepared.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20go%20back%20to%20the%20example%20of%20TVs%20%E2%80%94%20the%20great%20American%20escape.%20Televisions%2C%20like%20many%20consumer%20electronics%2C%20have%20gone%20down%20in%20price%20even%20as%20they've%20gotten%20better%20over%20the%20years.%20According%20to%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%2C%20television%20prices%20have%20decreased%20by%2098%25%20since%202000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20why%20the%20prices%20fall%20is%20because%20of%20business%20investment%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Paul%20Gagnon%2C%20a%20vice%20president%20and%20industry%20advisor%20on%20consumer%20technology%20at%20Circana%2C%20a%20market%20research%20firm%2C%20adding%20that%20companies%20invest%20%26quot%3Bcontinuously%20in%20new%20manufacturing%20facilities%20that%20are%20more%20efficient%20and%20therefore%20can%20produce%20for%20at%20least%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20money%20a%20product%20that%20has%20a%20lot%20more%20performance%2C%20or%20for%20less%20money%2C%20something%20that's%20larger.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20this%20activity%2C%20however%2C%20is%20taking%20place%20outside%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatrick%20Horner%2C%20a%20practice%20leader%20in%20TV%20set%20research%20at%20Omdia%2C%20a%20tech%20advisory%20firm%2C%20explained%20that%2010%20years%20ago%2C%2049%25%20of%20assembly%20for%20televisions%20imported%20into%20the%20US%20was%20happening%20in%20China.%20But%20after%20Trump's%20first%20term%20and%20the%20tariffs%20he%20put%20in%20place%20on%20China%20then%2C%20manufacturers%20moved%20more%20of%20their%20assembly%20operations%20to%20Mexico.%20Now%2C%20around%2060%25%20of%20American%20TV%20imports%20are%20made%20there.%20You%20can%20see%20the%20problem%3A%20In%20his%20second%20term%2C%20Trump%20has%20announced%2020%25%20additional%20tariffs%20on%20top%20of%20existing%20tariffs%20on%20China%2C%20and%20he's%20also%20threatening%20a%2025%25%20tariff%20on%20imports%20from%20Mexico%20that's%20(for%20now)%20supposed%20to%20be%20implemented%20in%20April.%20Omdia%20estimates%20manufacturers%20with%20existing%20factories%20could%20shift%20partial%20production%20to%20tariff-free%20countries%20in%20six%20months%20to%20a%20year%2C%20but%20building%20a%20new%20factory%20would%20take%20years.%20And%2C%20again%2C%20no%20one%20knows%20what%20Trump's%20next%20target%20could%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTV%20makers%20are%20looking%20into%20shifting%20some%20assembly%20out%20of%20Mexico%20and%20relocating%20it%20to%20someplace%20that%20doesn't%20have%20tariffs%2C%26quot%3B%20Horner%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20thing%20is%2C%20Trump%20could%20very%20much%20say%2C%20'Hey%2C%20Vietnam's%20on%20the%20radar%20screen%2C%20now%20they're%20getting%20the%2025%25%20tariff.'%20I%20don't%20think%20that%20anybody%20can%20accurately%20predict%20where%20the%20next%20tariff%20action%20is%20going%20to%20take%20place.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGagnon%20said%20some%20particular%20factors%20kept%20prices%20on%20TVs%20from%20going%20up%20too%20much%20in%20response%20to%20Trump's%20tariffs%20in%202018%20and%202019.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20retailers%20bought%20extra%20inventory%20to%20try%20to%20get%20ahead%20of%20price%20increases%20and%20it%20happened%20at%20a%20moment%20when%20supply%20chains%20to%20make%20critical%20components%20were%20expanding%20and%20pushing%20prices%20down.%20%26quot%3BEven%20though%20the%20tariffs%20caused%20the%20costs%20to%20go%20up%20on%20TVs%20imported%20from%20China%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20components%20of%20the%20TV%20went%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20The%20context%20now%20is%20different.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20pretty%20hard%20to%20see%20how%20an%20increase%20of%2025%25%20on%20the%20imported%20cost%20of%20a%20TV%20from%20Mexico%20to%20the%20US%2C%20given%20the%20profit%20margins%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20TVs%2C%20wouldn't%20result%20in%20a%20price%20increase%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20a%20bad%20thing%20to%20contemplate%20the%20end%20of%20the%20era%20of%20cheap%20stuff.%20The%20rate%20at%20which%20we're%20able%20to%20accumulate%20things%20without%20having%20to%20think%20about%20the%20trade-offs%20%E2%80%94%20environmental%2C%20labor-related%2C%20or%20otherwise%20%E2%80%94%20is%20alarming.%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20sound%20like%20a%20scold%20here%2C%20but%20our%20kids%20don't%20need%20so%20many%20toys%2C%20our%20closets%20don't%20need%20to%20be%20so%20full%2C%20and%20that%20barely%20old%20phone%20doesn't%20need%20to%20be%20swapped%20out.%20Getting%20a%20new%20fun%20thing%20may%20deliver%20a%20temporary%20endorphin%20hit%2C%20but%20most%20research%20shows%20it%20doesn't%20make%20us%20happier%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20It's%20not%20our%20fault%20we're%20like%20this.%20Corporations%20and%20marketers%20have%20turned%20us%20into%20stuffmongers%2C%20and%20even%20our%20political%20leaders%20encourage%20us%20to%20keep%20buying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20and%20when%20tariffs%20start%20to%20increase%20prices%20and%20make%20even%20the%20most%20reachable%20things%20unreachable%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20feel%20annoying%20and%20unfair.%20Goods%20aren't%20going%20to%20become%20higher%20quality%20overnight%3B%20tariffs%20will%20just%20make%20them%20costlier.%20That%20TV%20isn't%20made%20to%20be%20fixed%20when%20it%20breaks%3B%20it's%20made%20to%20be%20replaced%2C%20whatever%20the%20price%20of%20said%20replacement.%20Fixing%20something%20isn't%20just%20a%20physical%20skill%2C%20Strasser%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20it's%20an%20emotional%20skill%20and%20a%20way%20of%20framing%20your%20relationship%20to%20material%20goods%20that's%20just%20completely%20different%20from%20anything%20that%20we've%20experienced%20in%20the%20last%2050%2C%2060%2C%2070%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20it%20or%20not%2C%20the%20American%20dream%20is%20a%20little%20bit%20about%20access%20to%20cheap%20stuff.%20It's%20that%20giant%20TV%20that%20at%20least%20lets%20you%20watch%20the%20football%20game%20(assuming%20you%20can%20find%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flive-sports-streaming-guide-nfl-nba-mlb-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%