your-body-calories-weight-gain-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20all%20calories%20are%20created%20equal%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20far%20from%20it.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flancet%2Farticle%2FPIIS0140-6736%252800%252904041-1%2Fabstract%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EResearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20long%20shown%20that%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-happens-when-you-eat-too-much-sugar-2017-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecalorie%20of%20liquid%20sugar%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20not%20metabolized%20in%20the%20same%20manner%20as%20a%20calorie%20of%20whole%20grain%2C%20for%20example%2C%20or%20a%20calorie%20of%20fruit%20or%20nuts.%20Those%20calories%20have%20fiber%2C%20vitamins%2C%20and%20other%20nutrients%20that%20are%20not%20present%20in%20soda.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoke%20also%20promotes%20the%20related%20message%20of%20%26quot%3Benergy%20balance.%26quot%3B%20The%20simplest%20energy%20balance%20argument%20posits%20that%20a%20calorie%20of%20food%20will%20be%20metabolized%20the%20same%20whether%20it%20comes%20from%20cashews%2C%20kale%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoca-cola-coke-zero-earnings-revenues-fall-beat-analyst-expectations-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECoca-Cola%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20consumers%20should%20focus%20not%20on%20the%20type%20of%20food%20but%20on%20trying%20to%20burn%20as%20many%20calories%20as%20they%20consume.%20Coke%20has%20been%20especially%20interested%20in%20emphasizing%20the%20calories-out%20side%20of%20the%20equation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20focus%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoke-funded-research-group-disbands-2015-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGlobal%20Energy%20Balance%20Network%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20organization%20launched%20in%202014%20by%20researchers%20affiliated%20with%20the%20University%20of%20Colorado%20and%20the%20University%20of%20South%20Carolina.%20One%20of%20the%20academics%2C%20Steven%20Blair%2C%20did%20yeoman's%20work%20to%20shift%20Americans'%20focus%20from%20the%20elements%20of%20the%20diet%20to%20the%20concept%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoke-research-emphasizes-exercise-for-weight-loss-2015-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebalancing%20calories%20in%20and%20calories%20out%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20a%20video%20for%20the%20organization%2C%20Blair%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BMost%20of%20the%20focus%2C%20in%20the%20popular%20media%2C%20in%20the%20scientific%20press%2C%20is%20'Aww%2C%20they're%20eating%20too%20much%2C%20eating%20too%20much%2C%20eating%20too%20much.'%20Blaming%20fast%20foods%2C%20blaming%20sugary%20drinks%2C%20and%20so%20on%2C%20and%20there's%20really%20virtually%20no%20compelling%20evidence%20that%20that%20in%20fact%20is%20the%20cause.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20a%20New%20York%20Times%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.nytimes.com%2Fwell.blogs.nytimes.com%2F2015%2F08%2F09%2Fcoca-cola-funds-scientists-who-shift-blame-for-obesity-away-from-bad-diets%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpos%C3%A9%3C%2Fa%3E%20revealed%20that%20the%20Global%20Energy%20Balance%20Network%20was%20simply%20a%20front%20group%20for%20Coca-Cola.%20The%20corporation%20had%20funded%20it%20and%20guided%20it%20since%20its%20inception%20but%20wanted%20it%20to%20appear%20independent.%20This%20prompted%20a%20very%20public%20apology%20from%20Coke's%20then-CEO%20Muhtar%20Kent%2C%20who%20penned%20a%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20column%20titled%20%26quot%3BWe'll%20do%20better.%26quot%3B%20Coca-Cola%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20multiple%20requests%20for%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20was%20far%20from%20the%20only%20misleading%20messaging%20Coke%20had%20spread.%20In%20a%20May%202013%20blog%20post%2C%20Coca-Cola%20trumpeted%20its%20success%20in%20removing%20calories%20from%20the%20American%20diet%20through%20changing%20its%20product%20formulation%2C%20portion%20size%2C%20and%20promotion.%20%26quot%3BYesterday%2C%20America's%20top%20food%20and%20beverage%20manufacturers%20announced%20an%20important%20milestone%3A%20more%20than%201.5%20trillion%20calories%20have%20been%20removed%20from%20the%20US%20marketplace%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20now-removed%20post%20read.%20%26quot%3BThis%20achievement%20is%20the%20result%20of%20efforts%20made%20by%20the%20Healthy%20Weight%20Commitment%20Foundation%20(HWCF)%2C%20a%20coalition%20of%2016%20food%20and%20beverage%20corporate%20partners%2C%20including%20The%20Coca-Cola%20Company%2C%20and%20over%20230%20organizations%2C%20who%20are%20working%20together%20to%20help%20reduce%20obesity%2C%20especially%20childhood%20obesity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20post%20ran%20beneath%20a%20photo%20of%20the%20former%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%20secretary%20Dan%20Glickman%2C%20Lisa%20Gable%20of%20HWCF%2C%20and%20the%20author%20Hank%20Cardello%20at%20an%20event%20sponsored%20by%20the%20Obesity%20Solutions%20Initiative%20at%20the%20Hudson%20Institute.%20While%20the%20photo%20appears%20to%20be%20three%20independent%20experts%20cordially%20discussing%20the%20problem%20of%20obesity%2C%20the%20whole%20event%20was%20paid%20for%20by%20Coke%2C%20Pepsi%2C%20and%20other%20food%20corporations.%20Coke%20alone%20had%20given%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20to%20the%20Hudson%20Institute%20and%20%245%20million%20to%20HWCF.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20the%20company%20didn't%20mention%20is%20that%20Coca-Cola%20could%20remove%20far%20more%20calories%20from%20the%20marketplace%20in%20a%20heartbeat%20by%20taking%20full-sugar%20beverages%20off%20the%20market%20or%20reducing%20its%20advertising%20of%20those%20products.%20Not%20only%20does%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstrategies-coca-cola-used-to-become-an-iconic-brand-2016-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaggressively%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20these%20calorie-dense%20drinks%2C%20but%20it%20continues%20to%20introduce%20new%20Coke%20blends%20that%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoca-cola-launches-drink-mixers-for-whiskey-rum-tequila-fans-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECoca-Cola%20Spiced%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20even%20more%20sugar%20than%20the%20original%20Coca-Cola.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoke%20is%20in%20the%20business%20of%20selling%20sugar%20water.%20If%20it%20tries%20to%20reduce%20sales%20of%20its%20products%2C%20it%20would%20be%20violating%20its%20obligations%20to%20its%20shareholders.%20(Woe%20to%20the%20CEO%20who%20announces%20on%20an%20earnings%20call%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3BWe%20did%20it%2C%20we%20finally%20succeeded%20in%20reducing%20the%20amount%20of%20Coke%20we%20sell%2C%20thus%20reducing%20calories!%26quot%3B)%20What%20is%20unexpected%20is%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-coca-cola-fumbled-efforts-grow-small-beverage-brands-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECoca-Cola%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20concurrently%20sell%20more%20sugar-sweetened%20beverages%20than%20any%20other%20corporation%20while%20taking%20credit%20for%20reducing%20calories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20front%20group%20ended%20up%20taking%20the%20pro-sugar%20stance%20a%20bit%20too%20far.%20The%20International%20Life%20Sciences%20Institute%2C%20founded%20in%20the%201980s%20by%20a%20Coca-Cola%20executive%2C%20spent%20decades%20spinning%20food%20science%20in%20favor%20of%20its%20corporate%20funders%2C%20including%20Hershey%2C%20Kraft%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkelloggs-cereal-for-dinner-meal-backlash-price-inflation-pilnick-money-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKellogg%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20when%20it%20funded%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F27992898%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2016%20research%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20critiquing%20the%20growing%20body%20of%20science%20on%20the%20health%20r