bit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20counteract%20this%2C%20astronauts%20use%20three%20exercise%20machines%20on%20the%20ISS%2C%20including%20a%202009-installed%20resistance%20device%20that%20simulates%20free%20weights%20using%20vacuum%20tubes%20and%20flywheel%20cables.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20two-hour%20daily%20workout%20keeps%20them%20in%20shape.%20%26quot%3BThe%20best%20results%20that%20we%20have%20to%20show%20that%20we're%20being%20very%20effective%20is%20that%20we%20don't%20really%20have%20a%20fracture%20problem%20in%20astronauts%20when%20they%20return%20to%20the%20ground%2C%26quot%3B%20though%20bone%20loss%20is%20still%20detectable%20on%20scans%2C%20Bokhari%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBalance%20disruption%20is%20another%20issue%2C%20added%20Emmanuel%20Urquieta%2C%20vice%20chair%20of%20Aerospace%20Medicine%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Central%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20happens%20to%20every%20single%20astronaut%2C%20even%20those%20who%20go%20into%20space%20just%20for%20a%20few%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20AFP%2C%20as%20they%20work%20to%20rebuild%20trust%20in%20their%20inner%20ear.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAstronauts%20must%20retrain%20their%20bodies%20during%20NASA's%2045-day%20post-mission%20rehabilitation%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20challenge%20is%20%26quot%3Bfluid%20shift%26quot%3B%20--%20the%20redistribution%20of%20bodily%20fluids%20toward%20the%20head%20in%20microgravity.%20This%20can%20increase%20calcium%20levels%20in%20urine%2C%20raising%20the%20risk%20of%20kidney%20stones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFluid%20shifts%20might%20also%20contribute%20to%20increased%20intracranial%20pressure%2C%20altering%20the%20shape%20of%20the%20eyeball%20and%20causing%20spaceflight-associated%20neuro-ocular%20syndrome%20(SANS)%2C%20causing%20mild-to-moderate%20vision%20impairment.%20Another%20theory%20suggests%20raised%20carbon%20dioxide%20levels%20are%20the%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20at%20least%20one%20case%2C%20the%20effects%20have%20been%20beneficial.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20a%20pretty%20severe%20case%20of%20SANS%2C%26quot%3B%20NASA%20astronaut%20Jessica%20Meir%20said%20before%20the%20latest%20launch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20launched%2C%20I%20wore%20glasses%20and%20contacts%2C%20but%20due%20to%20globe%20flattening%2C%20I%20now%20have%2020%2F15%20vision%20--%20most%20expensive%20corrective%20surgery%20possible.%20Thank%20you%2C%20taxpayers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EManaging%20radiation%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERadiation%20levels%20aboard%20the%20ISS%20are%20higher%20than%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20as%20it%20passes%20through%20through%20the%20Van%20Allen%20radiation%20belt%2C%20but%20Earth's%20magnetic%20field%20still%20provides%20significant%20protection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20shielding%20is%20crucial%2C%20as%20NASA%20aims%20to%20limit%20astronauts'%20increased%20lifetime%20cancer%20risk%20to%20within%20three%20percent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20missions%20to%20the%20Moon%20and%20Mars%20will%20give%20astronauts%20far%20greater%20exposure%2C%20explained%20astrophysicist%20Siegfried%20Eggl.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFuture%20space%20probes%20could%20provide%20some%20warning%20time%20for%20high-radiation%20events%2C%20such%20coronal%20mass%20ejections%20--%20plasma%20clouds%20from%20the%20Sun%20--%20but%20cosmic%20radiation%20remains%20unpredictable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShielding%20is%20best%20done%20with%20heavy%20materials%20like%20lead%20or%20water%2C%20but%20you%20need%20vast%20quantities%20of%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Eggl%2C%20of%20University%20of%20Illinois%20Urbana-Champaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArtificial%20gravity%2C%20created%20by%20rotating%20spacecraft%20frames%2C%20could%20help%20astronauts%20stay%20functional%20upon%20arrival%20after%20a%20nine-month%20journey%20to%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlternatively%2C%20a%20spacecraft%20could%20use%20powerful%20acceleration%20and%20deceleration%20that%20matches%20the%20force%20of%20Earth's%20gravity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20approach%20would%20be%20speedier%20--%20reducing%20radiation%20exposure%20risks%20--%20but%20requires%20nuclear%20propulsion%20technologies%20that%20don't%20yet%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPreventing%20infighting%20among%20teams%20will%20be%20critical%2C%20said%20Joseph%20Keebler%2C%20a%20psychologist%20at%20Embry-Riddle%20Aeronautical%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BImagine%20being%20stuck%20in%20a%20van%20with%20anybody%20for%20three%20years%3A%20these%20vessels%20aren't%20that%20big%2C%20there's%20no%20privacy%2C%20there's%20no%20backyard%20to%20go%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20really%20commend%20astronauts%20that%20commit%20to%20this.%20It's%20an%20unfathomable%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742274780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2F87sir5ek_butch-wilmore-and-suni-williams-_625x300_12_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsunita-williams-butch-wilmore-return-balance-vision-issues-what-happens-to-human-body-after-9-months-in-space-7948325%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bone%20and%20muscle%20deterioration%2C%20radiation%20exposure%2C%20vision%20impairment%20--%20these%20are%20just%20a%20few%20of%20the%20challenges%20space%20travelers%20face%20on%20long-duration%20missions%2C%20even%20before%20considering%20the%20psychological%20toll%20of%20isolation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsunita-williams-butch-wilmore-return-balance-vision-issues-what-happens-to-human-body-after-9-months-in-space-7948325%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Apple%20improves%20stability%2C%20fi